Pour the @Water for the Rice{300%milliliter} into a #medium saucepan{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%grams}, @Salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the #lid{}.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a #large bowl{}, combine half the garlic, @North Indian Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Panko Breadcrumbs{10%grams}, @Salt for the Breadcrumbs{1/4%tsp} and @Water for the Breadcrumbs{1%tbsp}, then add the @Lamb Mince{200%grams}.

Season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands. Roll into evenly-sized balls, 5 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the meatballs and fry until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Stir in the remaining garlic and @Rogan Josh Curry Paste{50%grams}. Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Pour in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Sugar for the Sauce{1%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{100%milliliter} and @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}.

Season with salt and pepper, then cover with a lid or foil and simmer until the meatballs are cooked, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Once the meatballs are cooked, stir in the @Baby Spinach{100%grams} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, then share between your plates.

Top the rice with the Rogan Josh style curry and meatballs.

Drizzle with @Greek Style Natural Yoghurt{75%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!